<!-- SELF DEFENSE -->
<section id="selfdefense">
  <div class="section-tag">🥋 Protect Yourself</div>
  <h2>Self Defense Techniques</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">No experience needed. These moves create 2–5 seconds — enough time to escape.</p>
  <div class="sd-grid">
    <div class="sd-card"><div class="sd-icon">👊</div><div class="sd-level">⭐ Beginner — Learn this first</div><h4>Wrist Grab Escape</h4><ol><li>Rotate your wrist toward the attacker's thumb — the weakest grip point</li><li>Pull sharply toward your own body in one swift motion</li><li>Step back immediately to create distance</li><li>Shout loudly to attract bystanders, then run</li></ol></div>
    <div class="sd-card"><div class="sd-icon">🦵</div><div class="sd-level">⭐ Beginner — High impact</div><h4>Knee Strike</h4><ol><li>If grabbed from the front — do not struggle yet, stay calm</li><li>Grab the attacker's shoulders for balance</li><li>Drive your knee sharply upward into the groin with full force</li><li>Run and shout immediately</li></ol></div>
    <div class="sd-card"><div class="sd-icon">🤜</div><div class="sd-level">⭐⭐ Intermediate</div><h4>Palm Strike to Nose</h4><ol><li>Fingers bent back, palm flat — NOT a closed fist</li><li>Strike sharply upward toward the bridge of the nose</li><li>Drive from your hip — use whole body weight</li><li>Follow with a second strike if needed, then escape</li></ol></div>
    <div class="sd-card"><div class="sd-icon">😤</div><div class="sd-level">⭐⭐ Intermediate</div><h4>Bear Hug Escape</h4><ol><li>The moment grabbed from behind — drop your weight by bending knees</li><li>Stomp hard on the attacker's foot with your heel</li><li>Throw your head backward sharply into their face</li><li>Spin, elbow strike to ribs, run immediately</li></ol></div>
    <div class="sd-card"><div class="sd-icon">🔑</div><div class="sd-level">⭐ Beginner — Always Accessible</div><h4>Keys & Objects as Tools</h4><ol><li>Hold keys between fingers when walking alone at night</li><li>A firm jab with keys to the face creates an opening to escape</li><li>Pepper spray is legal in India — carry it always</li><li>Any rigid object (umbrella, water bottle) can be used defensively</li></ol></div>
    <div class="sd-card"><div class="sd-icon">🧠</div><div class="sd-level">⭐ The Most Important Defense</div><h4>Mental Preparedness</h4><ol><li>Stay aware at all times — no earphones in both ears</li><li>Make confident eye contact — signals you are not an easy target</li><li>Shout "FIRE!" not "Help" — people respond to fire faster</li><li>Trust your gut instantly — if it feels wrong, leave</li></ol></div>
  </div>
</section>

