<!-- RIGHTS -->
<section id="rights">
  <div class="section-tag">⚖️ Know Your Rights</div>
  <h2>Women's Rights & Indian Laws</h2>
  <p class="section-sub">These laws are your legal shield. Know them — and use them without hesitation anywhere in Himachal Pradesh.</p>
  <div class="rights-grid">
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Workplace</div><h4>POSH Act — Sexual Harassment at Work</h4><p>Every workplace with 10+ employees must have a functioning ICC. File within 3 months. Your identity is protected and retaliation is a separate punishable offense.</p><div class="right-law">Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace Act, 2013</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Home Safety</div><h4>Domestic Violence Protection</h4><p>Physical, emotional, sexual, verbal, and economic abuse are ALL covered. You can get a Protection Order, Residence Order, and Monetary Relief — even against in-laws.</p><div class="right-law">Protection of Women from Domestic Violence Act, 2005</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Police Rights</div><h4>Zero FIR — File Anywhere in India</h4><p>You can file an FIR at ANY police station regardless of jurisdiction. Police CANNOT refuse — doing so is a criminal offense under Section 166A IPC.</p><div class="right-law">Criminal Procedure Code — 2013 Amendment</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Survivor Rights</div><h4>Statement at Home — Assault Survivors</h4><p>A survivor cannot be called to a police station alone at night. Her statement is recorded at home by a magistrate. Her identity cannot be revealed by police or media.</p><div class="right-law">Section 164 CrPC + IPC Section 228A</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Legal Aid</div><h4>Right to Free Legal Representation</h4><p>Every woman victim of crime gets completely free legal services — advocate, court fees, and documentation — from the District Legal Services Authority in HP.</p><div class="right-law">Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Work Rights</div><h4>Maternity Benefits — 26 Weeks</h4><p>26 weeks of fully paid maternity leave. No employer can fire or demote a pregnant woman. Nursing breaks must be provided. Work-from-home must be considered on return.</p><div class="right-law">Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, 2017</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Online Safety</div><h4>Cyber Crime Against Women</h4><p>Morphed images, cyberstalking, sextortion, and online harassment are punishable with up to 3 years imprisonment. Report at cybercrime.gov.in or 1930.</p><div class="right-law">IT Act 2000 + IPC Sections 354D, 509</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="right-tag">Night Safety</div><h4>Right to Safe Night Shift Transport</h4><p>Women in night shifts must be provided safe cab transport with a female security guard. Employers who fail are liable under the Factories Act — report to HP Labour Department.</p><div class="right-law">Factories Act + Industrial Employment Rules</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

